[2026-07-12] tests: create-<variant> test ids on landing cards; E2E helper updated. All 5 E2E still pass.
[2026-07-12] verify(ui): typecheck clean; unit 33/33; next build OK; E2E 5/5.
[2026-07-12] SCOPED (not built): friends/add, direct messaging with sent/delivered/seen, notifications, profile editing.
    — These require persistent accounts + a presence/social backend; planned as a separate milestone (see chat). Deferred to keep the "100% correct" bar.

[2026-07-12] privacy: Hardened the room-privacy toggle client-side — treats a missing isPublic as public (default), so a room never shows "Private"
    incorrectly. The toggle logic was already correct; a room showing Private with a dead button indicates a STALE realtime server
    (privacy shipped in 8952355, after the Dockerfile fix 49df50a). Fix on the deployment side = redeploy Render to latest main.
    Added an E2E ("privacy: host can toggle a room between public and private") proving the round-trip works on current code.
[2026-07-12] responsive: viewport meta (width=device-width); room header buttons collapse to icons on mobile (labels hidden < sm);
    game grid uses minmax(0,1fr) + min-w-0 so the board never overflows; card word text scales down (text-[9px]) and wraps on small screens;
    landing header wraps. Verified across the layout.
[2026-07-12] verify(privacy/responsive): typecheck clean; unit 33/33; next build OK; E2E 6/6.

[2026-07-12] social: Implemented the full social platform (account-only; guests keep quick play).
    — DB models: FriendRequest, Friendship (normalised pair), DirectMessage (deliveredAt/seenAt), Notification. server/db/social.ts helpers.
    — server/social/socialServer.ts: presence registry (userId -> sockets), friends (add/accept/decline/remove, auto-accept reverse request),
      game invites (ping a friend to your room), DMs with sent/delivered/seen receipts (deliver-on-connect for offline msgs), notifications.
      Runs alongside GameServer on the same io; wired into index.ts + standalone.ts.
    — Profile: PATCH /api/profile updates displayName and reissues the JWT.
    — Client: useSocial hook + SocialDock (floating hub) — friends & requests, presence dots, DM threads with receipts,
      notifications with Join-invite, inline display-name edit. Rendered on landing + in room (invite enabled in room).
    — Verified: typecheck clean; a DB smoke test (scripts/smoke-social.ts) exercised friends/requests/DMs/receipts/notifications end-to-end
      against real Neon Postgres and passed (temp users cleaned up); next build OK; existing E2E 6/6 (guest flows unaffected — dock is account-only).
[2026-07-12] deploy(db): Pushed the new social tables to Neon (prisma db push). Any future schema change needs the same on the DB.

[2026-07-12] fix(leave): Leaving the room via in-app navigation (logo / Back / anything that isn't Exit) now emits room:leave so other
    players see you go. useRoom emits room:leave on unmount, guarded by a joinedRef so it only fires after a successful join and NOT on a
    hard reload/tab-close (React runs no cleanup there) — so reconnection via the disconnect grace still works.
[2026-07-12] social(search): Added user search — user:search socket event + social.searchUsers (username/displayName, case-insensitive).
    FriendsTab is now a live search-and-add (250ms debounce) showing matches with Add buttons and Friend/Sent status.
    (Usernames are already unique — enforced at register with a 409 — and each account already gets a cuid id.)
[2026-07-12] footer: Added a "Built by Decodrs" link (https://decodrs.com) to the landing footer.
[2026-07-12] verify(leave/search/footer): typecheck clean; unit 33/33; next build OK; E2E 6/6.
[2026-07-12] invite: Invite friends to a room from the room while team spots are open. Server gates game:invite on
    spots (lobby + not full) via a RoomManager now shared between GameServer and SocialServer. Web: invite button shown
    only when in-room and spots available; invite notifications gained Accept (join) + Decline. Verified web E2E 6/6.
[2026-07-12] mobile(social): Added accounts (login/register via web API), socket auth token + reconnect, a Friends/Account
    screen (search/add friends, requests, invites), a global game-invite Alert (Accept -> join room / Decline), and an
    in-room "Invite friends" picker (spots-gated). Mobile typecheck clean; Metro bundle OK.
[2026-07-12] ui: Made overlays opaque for readability — Modal (Settings/Rules) and the SocialDock panel now use the solid
    surface token instead of the translucent one. Prevents the see-through, hard-to-read modal look.
[2026-07-12] theme: Added a prominent dark/light toggle (sun/moon) to the landing and room headers (in addition to Preferences),
    and converted the remaining hardcoded slate panels (Chat, CluePanel, TurnTimer, AuthPanel, players/join panels) to theme
    tokens so light mode is coherent across the app.
[2026-07-12] mobile-link: Landing shows a "Get the Android app (APK)" button when NEXT_PUBLIC_APK_URL is set.
[2026-07-12] matchmaking: Reworked Quick Match into a queue. match:find now (1) joins an existing open public room if one
    has space, else (2) waits in a queue — it NEVER creates a room for a lone player. A new room is created only when two
    compatible players are both waiting (variant-aware; "any" matches anything). Added match:cancel + match:found events;
    clients keep showing the "finding" state (globe on web, spinner+Cancel on mobile) until matched. Room fill capped (MATCH_CAP).
[2026-07-12] rules: Exactly one clue-giver (spymaster) per team. setRole spymaster is rejected if the team already has one,
    and a spymaster switching to a team that already has one is demoted to operative. Auto-placement already seats only one.
[2026-07-12] tests: Rewrote matchmaking E2E (lone searcher waits; two searchers pair; joins existing public room) and reset
    teams before manual assignment in the full-game tests (to respect the one-spymaster rule). All 7 E2E pass.
